dct_description_sm: Geological Survey of New Jersey. Atlas Sheet 23 (1903) New Jersey Geological Survey Relief shown by 10 to 20 ft contour interval. Depth shown by soundings in feet at low tide. Title is not given. Region covered: northern Bergen and eastern Passaic counties. Original survey 1882, principal features revised 1903,1923, 1932. Original survey and revisions to 1903 made under direction of C.C. Vermeule, Topographer. Revision of 1923 by L.P. Plummer, Topographic Engineer."
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : Geological Survey of New Jersey, 1903.
